snippet: Conservative factions that already dominate the Parliament seemed to be cruising to victory Friday in a second round of elections to the 290-member assembly.
abstract: Election officials in Iran report a high voter turnout in runoff parliamentary elections, following a nationwide vote in which the conservatives won a resounding victory; outcome is not expected to provide much, if any, comfort for Pres Mahmoud Ahmadinejad, who had a rocky relationship with the departing Parliament.
lead_paragraph: Conservative factions that already dominate the Parliament seemed to be cruising to victory Friday in a second round of elections to the 290-member assembly.

headline.main: Iranians Vote in a Runoff for Parliament
headline.print_headline: Iranians Vote In a Runoff For Parliament
